@page "/terms"
@layout PublicLayout

<PageTitle>Terms of Service — Nornis</PageTitle>

<article class="nornis-public-page">
    <div class="nornis-eyebrow">Terms of Service</div>
    <h1>The short, honest version</h1>
    <p class="nornis-public-updated">Last updated: July 2026</p>

    <h2>The service</h2>
    <p>
        Nornis provides tools for capturing tabletop world material and deriving structured
        world knowledge from it, including AI-assisted extraction and question answering. The
        service is provided as-is, and features may change as it evolves — see the
        <a href="/changelog">change log</a>.
    </p>

    <h2>Your content</h2>
    <p>
        You own what you put into Nornis and what Nornis derives from it. You grant us only the
        rights needed to operate the service: storing your content, processing it with our AI
        provider when you request it, and displaying it to the world members you've chosen.
        Don't upload content you don't have the right to use.
    </p>

    <h2>AI-generated content</h2>
    <p>
        Extraction proposals and Loremaster answers are generated by AI and can be wrong. Nornis
        is designed so that a person reviews AI proposals before they become accepted world
        knowledge — that review is your responsibility, and accepted canon reflects your
        decisions, not ours.
    </p>

    <h2>Acceptable use</h2>
    <p>
        Use Nornis for its purpose: recording and exploring your worlds. Don't attempt to
        access other users' worlds, probe or disrupt the service, or use it to store material
        that is illegal or infringes others' rights.
    </p>

    <h2>Liability</h2>
    <p>
        To the maximum extent permitted by law, Nornis is provided without warranties, and our
        liability is limited to the amount you've paid for the service. Keep your own copies of
        source material that matters to you.
    </p>
</article>
